          <msContents>
            <summary>Small manuscript for private or public recitation or prayer, dedicated the veneration of one's spiritual guide or guru considered, in this context, a manifestation of the Hindu deity Śiva on earth. Presented as a dialogue between the deity Śiva (in the form of Īśvara) and the goddess Pārvatī.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Gurugītā</title>
              <title type="vernacular">गुरुगीता</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: śrīskaṃdapurāṇuttarakhaṃḍe īśvarapārvatīsaṃvāde gurugītāsamāptam astu rāmārpaṇam astu // (f. 10r-10v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
